---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Accessibility · Dayel Ostraco"
  description="Accessibility statement for dayelostra.co: built to WCAG 2.1 AA and checked by an automated axe-core gate on every change."
  robots="index,follow"
  bodyClass="min-h-screen"
>
  <Navbar home={false} />

  <main id="main-content" tabindex="-1" class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20 lg:py-28">
    <a href="/" class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-text-dim transition-colors hover:text-accent">
      <span class="font-semibold">/</span> Back to dayelostra.co
    </a>

    <p class="eyebrow mt-14">Statement</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-5xl">Accessibility</h1>

    <p class="mt-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-dim md:text-xl">
      This site is meant to work for everyone, and accessibility is checked automatically on every change, not audited once and forgotten.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-14 text-xl font-semibold">Standard</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-text-dim">
      The target conformance level is <span class="font-semibold text-accent">WCAG 2.1 AA</span>, the same technical bar the U.S. federal government harmonizes Section 508 to. Color, structure, and interaction are designed against that standard.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-xl font-semibold">Continuously enforced</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-text-dim">
      Every change to this site runs an automated <span class="font-semibold text-accent">axe-core</span> accessibility gate in continuous integration. A build with any WCAG A or AA violation does not ship. This statement therefore reflects a standard held on every commit, not a one-time pass.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-xl font-semibold">What is covered</h2>
    <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 leading-relaxed text-text-dim">
      <li><span class="font-semibold text-text">Contrast.</span> Text and interface contrast verified across both the light and dark sections of the site.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold text-text">Keyboard.</span> Full keyboard navigation with a visible focus indicator on every interactive element.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold text-text">Reduced motion.</span> Animations and transitions respect the <span class="font-mono text-sm">prefers-reduced-motion</span> setting.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold text-text">Reflow.</span> Content reflows without horizontal scrolling down to a 320px viewport.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold text-text">Structure.</span> Semantic headings, landmarks, image alternatives, and a skip-to-content link.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-xl font-semibold">Honest limitations</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-text-dim">
      Automated testing catches a large share of accessibility issues but not all of them; some WCAG criteria require human judgment. This is an ongoing commitment maintained alongside the site, not a formal third-party audit or VPAT. If something here does not work for you, treat it as a bug worth reporting.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-xl font-semibold">Report an issue</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-text-dim">
      Found a barrier? Email
      <a href="mailto:dayel.ostraco@proton.me" class="font-semibold text-accent underline decoration-accent/40 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:decoration-accent">dayel.ostraco@proton.me</a>
      and I will fix it.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-16 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-text-dim">Last reviewed: July 13, 2026</p>
  </main>

  <Footer />

  <script src="../scripts/main.js"></script>
</Layout>
